msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "You must install Red Hat Enterprise Linux&nbsp;6.3 Server on a system to use it as a virtualization host in a Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization environment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Download and Install Red Hat Enterprise Linux&nbsp;6.3 Server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Download and Install Red Hat Enterprise Linux&nbsp;6 Server on the target virtualization host, referring to the <citetitle>Red Hat Enterprise Linux&nbsp;6 Installation Guide</citetitle> for detailed instructions. Only the <package>Base</package> package group is required to use the virtualization host in a Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization environment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you are using directory services with no direct access to authentication files for user management, the <systemitem class=\"daemon\">vdsm</systemitem> package will fail to create the required system user when adding the host to Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization. To avoid this issue you must ensure that the authentication files required by the <command>useradd</command> command are locally accessible. Using a security policy with a mixture of local files and <application> LDAP</application> is recommended."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you intend to use Virtual Local Area Networks (<acronym>VLANs</acronym>) in your Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization environment, ensure that they are configured for access to the Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization Manager."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Result"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "You have installed Red Hat Enterprise Linux&nbsp;6.3 Server. You must however complete additional configuration tasks before adding the virtualization host to your Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization environment."
